              <td><span class="badge-ecosystem">Ecosystem</span></td>
              <td>MITRE ATLAS, NIST</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><a href="#bias-fairness">Bias, Fairness &amp; Discrimination</a></td>
              <td>Representational harm</td>
              <td><span class="badge-ecosystem">Ecosystem</span></td>
              <td>NIST AI RMF, EU AI Act</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Closing -->
    <section class="closing-section" id="protocol">
      <h2>SAPIEN Is a Protocol, Not a Single Test</h2>
      <p>The Safety Assessment Protocol for Intelligent Entity Networks provides a methodology for measuring AI behavioral failures: define behavioral dimensions, create calibrated scenarios, build scoring rubrics, and establish conformance requirements. Sycophantic drift scoring is the first published module because it was the least measured and most operationally dangerous gap. But the protocol is designed to extend. Each planned module follows the same structure &mdash; dimensions, scenarios, rubrics, conformance &mdash; applied to a different failure surface. The goal is a comprehensive behavioral safety measurement protocol that any organization can implement against any AI system.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Open Call -->
    <section class="opencall-section" id="contributors">
      <h2>Open Call for Contributors</h2>
      <p>SAPIEN is seeking domain experts to develop behavioral scoring modules across the AI safety landscape. Each module follows the SAPIEN methodology: define behavioral dimensions, create calibrated test scenarios, establish scoring rubrics, and publish conformance requirements.</p>

      <div class="module-roles">
        <div class="module-role">
          <h3>Agentic Safety Module</h3>
          <p>Define behavioral dimensions for AI systems that take real-world actions. Build scenarios that test whether agents maintain safety boundaries when using tools, browsing, executing code, or managing workflows under user pressure.</p>
          <p class="seeking"><em>Seeking: AI agent developers, tool-use safety researchers, agentic system red teamers</em></p>
        </div>
        <div class="module-role">
          <h3>Memory &amp; Context Integrity Module</h3>
          <p>Define dimensions for measuring how persistent memory and accumulated context degrade safety over time. Build multi-session test scenarios that capture trust accumulation and boundary erosion.</p>
          <p class="seeking"><em>Seeking: Researchers working on persistent AI systems, conversation memory safety, longitudinal AI evaluation</em></p>
        </div>
        <div class="module-role">
          <h3>Hallucination Persistence Module</h3>
          <p>Define dimensions for measuring whether models defend fabricated claims under questioning. Build scenarios that distinguish models that self-correct from those that double down.</p>
          <p class="seeking"><em>Seeking: Factuality researchers, grounding specialists, RAG safety engineers</em></p>
        </div>
        <div class="module-role">
          <h3>Cross-Domain Trust Transfer Module</h3>
          <p>Formalize the cross-domain pivot methodology from SAPIEN v1.1's Adversarial Simulation into a standalone scoring module with dedicated dimensions and scenarios.</p>
          <p class="seeking"><em>Seeking: Social engineering researchers, multi-domain safety evaluators, trust modeling specialists</em></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="contact-block">
        <p>Contact: <a href="mailto:contributors@sapienframework.org">contributors@sapienframework.org</a></p>
